<br>
&gt;Invading the most grim city in existence, taunting those around you, and then complaining when there are repurcussions. Dont like it? Dont invade.<br>
<br>
&gt;Young dark elves flocking about lalala and being social with the invading force. Those are your parents, friends, and young ones they're killing people. :P<br>
<br>
&gt;By invading and then telling me I can do nothing in response, you're forcing me into false RP. This is my characters home. When Im playing him, I revel in it. I try to imagine the sounds, and smells, etc. Asking me to pretend you arent there, to ignore my kin being killed around me, or to only respond with shouts is forcing me into bad RP imho.<br>
<br>
Long and short--dont like being trained, dont invade the city. I would expect to be trained were Valsharn to invade yours. I know the rule is no training, but cities are different whether you like it or not as several people pointed out. Not only that, but you got what you deserved with all the taunting you did. Big level 50s talking smack and then crying when they get trained. Fools. <br>
<br>
